UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1816
1 A RESOLUTION recognizing January 2026 as Kentucky Mentorship Month.
2 WHEREAS, mentorship plays a critical role in the personal, academic, and
3 professional development of young people by providing guidance, encouragement, and
4 positive role models; and
5 WHEREAS, research consistently demonstrates that young people with mentors are
6 more likely to succeed in school, pursue postsecondary education or workforce training,
7 maintain stable employment, and contribute positively to their communities; and
8 WHEREAS, strong mentoring relationships foster community connection by
9 bridging generations, strengthening families, and reinforcing shared values such as
10 responsibility, service, and perseverance; and
11 WHEREAS, mentors, including educators, employers, faith leaders, volunteers, and
12 community members, help young people navigate challenges, develop life skills, and
13 discover pathways to meaningful careers and civic engagement; and
14 WHEREAS, mentorship is especially vital in supporting youth who face barriers to
15 opportunity, helping to expand access to education, career exploration, and workforce
16 readiness across the Commonwealth; and
17 WHEREAS, Kentucky’s future economic strength and civic health depend upon
18 investing in young people today through intentional relationships that build confidence,
19 character, and connection to community;
20 NOW, THEREFORE,
21 Be it resolved by the Senate of the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of
22 Kentucky:
23 Section 1. The members of the Senate hereby recognize January 2026 as
24 Kentucky Mentorship Month.
25 Section 2. When the Senate adjourns this day, it recognizes and celebrates the
26 individuals, organizations, schools, businesses, and community groups that provide
27 mentorship and support to Kentucky’s youth.
